{"parse":{"title":"The Virtues of War","pageid":36240573,"revid":846849399,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><br />\n<i><b>The Virtues of War</b></i> is a 2004 <a href=\"/wiki/Historical_fiction\" title=\"Historical fiction\">historical fiction</a> novel by <a href=\"/wiki/Steven_Pressfield\" title=\"Steven Pressfield\">Steven Pressfield</a> that follows the life of <a href=\"/wiki/Alexander_the_Great\" title=\"Alexander the Great\">Alexander the Great</a>, told through the eyes of a <a href=\"/wiki/Ancient_Greece\" title=\"Ancient Greece\">Hellenic</a>-<a href=\"/wiki/Persia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Persia\">Persian</a> scribe serving under him during his campaigns into <a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">India</a>.  Alexander is recounting the events of his life to the young scholar just before he dies in <a href=\"/wiki/Babylon\" title=\"Babylon\">Babylon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Alexander first recounts of his younger days serving under his father, <a href=\"/wiki/Philip_II_of_Macedon\" title=\"Philip II of Macedon\">Philip II of Macedon</a>, and Philip's expansion of Macedonian hegemony throughout <a href=\"/wiki/Greece\" title=\"Greece\">Greece</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Thrace\" title=\"Thrace\">Thrace</a>.  After his father's assassination, Alexander assumes control of the Macedonian throne and re-subdues Greece. He invades the Persian empire, eventually conquering it all, and continues into <a href=\"/wiki/Afghanistan\" title=\"Afghanistan\">Afghanistan</a> and into <a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">India</a>.  The final battle fought is the <a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_the_Hydaspes\" title=\"Battle of the Hydaspes\">Battle of the Hydaspes</a> in which Alexander solidifies his rule over the Indians.\n</p><p>Throughout the novel, Alexander is portrayed as a benevolent king who only ever wanted to be a soldier, attain military glory, and treat his enemies with honor in the hopes of eventually making them his friends.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Virtues_of_War&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Kirkus_Reviews\" title=\"Kirkus Reviews\">Kirkus Reviews</a> praises Pressfield's writing calling it \"deft and graceful as always in his historical authenticity\". <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Virtues_of_War&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/The-Virtues-War-Novel-Alexander/dp/0553382055\">\"The Virtues of War: A Novel of Alexander the Great\"</a>. <i>Amazon</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Amazon&amp;rft.atitle=The+Virtues+of+War%3A+A+Novel+of+Alexander+the+Great&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FThe-Virtues-War-Novel-Alexander%2Fdp%2F0553382055&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Virtues+of+War\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.stevenpressfield.com/the-virtues-of-war/\">\"The Virtues of War\"</a>. <i>stevenpressfield.com</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=stevenpressfield.com&amp;rft.atitle=The+Virtues+of+War&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.stevenpressfield.com%2Fthe-virtues-of-war%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Virtues+of+War\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/steven-pressfield/the-virtues-of-war/\">\"THE VIRTUES OF WAR by Steven Pressfield - Kirkus Reviews\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=THE+VIRTUES+OF+WAR+by+Steven+Pressfield+-+Kirkus+Reviews&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kirkusreviews.com%2Fbook-reviews%2Fsteven-pressfield%2Fthe-virtues-of-war%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Virtues+of+War\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Works_by_Steven_Pressfield\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Steven_Pressfield\" title=\"Template